"Some businesses implement instant messaging software to facilitate company communication. Refrain from engaging in personal conversations, harassing or teasing coworkers, badmouthing supervisors or typing foul language when using a work chat application. Always conduct yourself in a professional manner when communicating at work.","Today, the majority of businesses monitor their employees in some fashion. Employers can remotely look on in real time as their staff performs job-related tasks. With a few thoughtful steps and appropriate behaviors, a worker can easily safeguard their personal privacy on the job."," "]},"id":"a0b5d74d-7740-4b4a-ad3f-0c66389f83d2","type":"text"}]],"body":null,"legacyId":"article_page_4759","url":"/privacy-in-the-workplace","authors":[{"email":"","slug":"barbara-applebaum","url":"/author/barbara-applebaum","dateCreated":"2019-04-17T20:46:58Z","name":"Barbara Applebaum","dateModified":"2019-04-17T20:46:58Z","id":"jtHnzr5xtW7Zdju7FZAWDY","dateImported":null,"site":"toptenreviews"}],"territories":["US","GB"],"companies":[],"dateCreated":"2010-08-12T20:58:31Z","datePublished":"2010-08-12T20:58:31Z","name":"Employee Monitoring Software: Protecting Your Privacy in the Workplace","synopsis":"Most employers give their employees a reasonable amount of workplace privacy. Few managers grow concerned when an employee occasionally visits a news website or sends an email home.","review":{},"strapline":"Most employers give their employees a reasonable amount of workplace privacy. Few managers grow concerned when an employee occasionally visits a news website or sends an email home.","language":"en","dateModified":"2010-08-20T15:20:29Z","id":"6xAjEd3WiQVUeNLCaoT8a3","meta":{"title":"Employee Monitoring Software: Protecting Your Privacy in the Workplace","description":"Visit Top Ten Reviews to read the latest reviews and opinions. Reviews are complete with product ratings and comparisons."},"products":[],"dateImported":"2019-04-17T20:54:13Z","type":"featu